classitems.description:
Creates a token out of the provided text.
Removes leading/trailing whitespaces and special characters.
Tokens, consisting of a single character after this process are discarded.
For urls, tokens with the type 'u' are created and for email-adresses,
tokens with the type 'e' respectively.

params.name: text
params.description: the text from which to create the token

params.name: parent
params.description: the parent element of the text

classitems.description: Represents a corpus of tokens

Function updates the amount of tokens belonging to the provided parent

If no entry exists for the token in the corpus, a new entry is created along 
with the corresponding parent entry. If the token is present, but the parent
entry not, the latter is added. Otherwise, the amount of tokens corresponding
to the given parent entry is incremented by 1. In all cases, the overall 
amount of occurrences of the provided token is incremented by 1.

params.name: token
params.description: the token for which to increment the amount

params.name: parent
params.description: the token's parent for which to increment the amount

classitems.description: Builds a corpus of tokens from the given elements

params.description:
the elements to tokenize (each entry in the array
must be an object with structure {text:String,parent:String}

params.name: language
params.description: country code for language

params.name: callback
params.description:
callback function to trigger after calculation is
finished. The corpus is passed to this function as an argument.

Implements a search result list, which can be used by all components.
The list updates itself, if a new query was issued and new results arrive.
Ratings are updated as well.
Required libs:
- jquery
- jquery.raty
- jquery-ui
Required css-files:
- eexcess.css
- searchResultList.css
- jquery-ui.css
Handlers for preview and rating can be customized via options, as well as the
path to the media folder and the path to the libs folder

See an usage example in /usage_examples searchResultList.js and searchResultList.html
